<h1>What is a University Response?</h1>
<p>A University Response is the answer to any common policy question at BYU-Idaho. A University Response can come by two different means:</p>
<ol>
<li>SRC Representatives work hard to bring global student issues to the University and propose changes. Whenever a policy cannot be changed we ask the administrator to write a University Response explaining why the change could not occur.</li>
<li>SRC Representatives will research commonly asked questions about University Policy</li>
</ol>
<p>Past&nbsp;University Responses:</p>
<p><a href="x43738.xml" target="_blank">Why do single students have to live in BYU-Idaho Approved Housing?</a></p>
<p><a href="x46876.xml">What resources are availabe for students struggling with same-gender attraction?</a></p>
<p><a href="x47094.xml">Concealed Weapons On Campus</a></p>
<p><a href="x47758.xml" target="_blank">BYU-Idaho Parking</a></p>
<p><a href="x51089.xml">Outside Vendors in the Crossroads</a></p>
<p><br />Our SRC Representatives are hard at work researching and finding more University Responses! Keep an eye on this page throughout the semester.</p>
